title: For Sale/Trade:  Mossberg 800 asm 308 , scope, ammo trade for ar15 , ak47 or make offer.
postcontent:
In excellent condition . Comes with a tasco high country 3x9x40 scope , 90 rounds of ammo and slang. I guess the Mossberg 800 asm is a rare gun . Make offer thanks. Call or text REDACTED.What is a Mossberg 308 bolt action rifle worth
This rifle was originally designed by Louis Seecamp and Carl Benson in the late 1960s for Montgomery Ward to sell in their stores. Montgomery Ward decided not to sell them, but Mossberg took up the type and sold it in its various incarnations into late 1970s. 
The Model 800 had a strangely-shaped S-shaped bolt handle - bent forward, then back. The rifle is well-made and looks good. Internally, the bolt is also unusual, having two rows of three lugs (most rifles only have one set of lugs). The extractor uses a rather short blade, but its spring is especially strong, saving space and giving the Model 800 reliable case ejection. The early versions used a walnut Monte Carlo-type half stock, with the pistol grip wrist having a plastic white cap and the buttplate having decorative white spacers. The pistol grip wrist and fore-end had impressed skip-line checkering. 


The model 800 had a few variations which affects the value, although not by much. Very Good condition would be worth $600 to $750. The model 810, about the same.

They sent it out to be Cerakoted in OD Green.  I paid just shy of $3400.00 with tax.  I require a WA. CPL for verification that you can legally own a firearm.  

Exactly 100 rounds downrange through this.  60 rounds of Federal XM80C and 40 rounds of PRVI 147 grain NATO.  I zeroed a scope with it, then did a couple mag dumps to check function of the rifle.  It shot without so much as a hiccup.  It was promptly given a complete Frog Lube treatment and stored in a temperature controlled gun safe.  

It's in mint condition, I have simply decided to go a different way with other calibers/platforms and don't need it. Plus, I could use the money more than the gun. Serious offers only please as I am not hurting to sell this rifle. I'm not interested in your baseball card collection, kittens, puppies, old cars, or your lifted toy trucks and 4x4's. 

 A little about Hogan: It's a gas piston driven rifle made by one of the best.  For those that don't know, Hogan used to build all of P.O.F.-U.S.A's rifles.  They still do work for many companies, to include building GA Arms Precision's sniper rifles for them.  

I'll include links for reviews done by world renowned and former world record longest shot U.S.M.C. MARSOC Sniper Steve Reichert.  This is one of the finest, if not the finest .308 platforms that your going to find.  

http://stevereichert.com/sniper-rifle-selection/

http://stevereichert.com/the-best-sniper-rifles-money-can-buy/

http://www.hoganguns.com/h-308/hr308SA-16.html

OPERATING SYSTEM:
Gas trap/piston operation, rotating bolt (short stroke system), reversible gas piston for suppressed or non-suppressed operation.
Unlike some other "op-rod" systems, on the HOGAN gun, op-rod springs have been eliminated due to possible damage and system failure during sustained firing of the gun. The HOGAN gun system has been designed and manufactured to greatly decrease/eliminate heat, carbon build-up, gas leaks, fouling and wear/tear on operating parts which can have an adverse effect on an operating system.
Each piece of operating system is hard chrome plated and/or melonite heat treated making them almost self lubricating and act as non stick surfaces making them easy to clean and maintain.
Operates in semi-automatic, but can be made full-auto for Military and Law Enforcement.

UPPER RECEIVER:
Billet machined from 7075 aluminum bar stock, (aircraft aluminum alloy), into a
2-piece railed upper receiver to fit our Free Floating Monolithic rail system
Electro-less *silicone Nickel on the interior (*depending on availability when rifle is shipped)
Finished in black, O.D. Green Tan or Clear anodize, NP3™ or Cerakote™ Dark Earth , O.D. Green, (depending on customer preference or gun design).

CHARGING HANDLE:
Billet machined from 7075 aluminum bar stock, manufactured with an oversized grip and locking latch.
Black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625, duo colored with electro less Nickel coating/black anodize to Mil-Spec 9625 or NP3™ coated, (depending on customer preference or firearm design).

HEAT SINK BARREL NUT and WEDGEBLOCK:
“Patented” oversized 3.375” heat sink barrel nut design billet machined from 6061
T-6 aluminum, heat treated and black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625
Provides strength, rigidity to rail system and works as a heat sink to greatly reduce heat buildup utilizing a larger surface area and cooling fins. Comes in sizes short, long
or ribbed to meet specifications of firearm design.
Wedgeblock comes in 2 styles fat for A3 flattop upper receiver or grooved for monolithic railed receiver, billet machined from 6061 T-6 aluminum extrusion, heat treated and black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625.

HANDGUARDS/RAILS:
Aircraft aluminum alloy precision machined from 6061 T-6 extrusion Free Floating Monolithic Tactical and Hunter hand guards or Monolithic top rail finished in black, O.D. Green, Tan, or Clear anodize, NP3™ or Cerakote™ Dark Earth or O.D. Green.

PISTON and OP ROD:
Reversible gas piston for suppressed or non-suppressed operation billet machined from 4140 high temp steel round bar, heat treated to Mil-Spec, ground to size, hard chrome plated. 
Tool steel op-rod, heat treated to Mil-Spec from PCS Company.

GAS BLOCK ASSEMBLY and GAS PLUG:
Gas block: billet machined from 4140 aircraft quality steel bar stock, heat treated to Mil-Spec.
Gas tube: 4130 aircraft quality tubing. Block and tube are joined then mated with barrel (matching serial#’s added), then melonite heat treated together.
Gas plug: billet machined from 4140/4142 steel bar, heat treated to Mil-Spec, ground to size, mag phosphate on top, NP3 coated, and/or chrome plated with blackened top.

BOLT and CARRIER:
.308 bolt: machined from 9310 steel bar stock, phosphate heat treated to Mil-Spec .308 and mag particle inspected, hard chrome plated.
Carrier: billet machined from single piece of 8620 steel - integral keyed steel bolt carrier (machined as one piece to leave key in place). Heat treated per Mil-Spec, Nickel Teflon plated.

HOGAN SPECIFICATIONS:
Smaller parts like springs, screws and washers are sourced from domestic manufacturers.
Everything in a HOGAN gun is 100% made in the U.S.A. All raw materials are manufactured from U.S. steel mills.
All heat treats, plating/coatings, are completed by U.S. owned and operated manufactures.
All accessory and component parts on weapon systems are from U.S. owned and operated manufacturers.
All HOGAN weapon systems are 100% pure American made.


BARREL:
Barrel blanks are supplied by Rock Creek Barrels, Inc. and completed to final specification at Hogan Guns.
Medium contour, hand lapped button twisted rifled, 6 fluted to improve rigidity and heat dissipation, reduce weight, improve accuracy by reducing barrel vibration when firing.
4150 Mil-B-11595 chrome moly vanadium alloy (machine gun rated).
70 Rockwell case hardened heat treated “5R” polygonal barrels are 2 times harder than Mil-Spec and hammer forged barrels.
Corrosion resistant and 10 times thicker and harder than Mil-Spec chromed lining. The treatment on the barrels causes zero imperfections and is extremely smooth which also enables the barrels to consistently achieve excellent accuracy.
Chamber: 7.62 x 51mm NATO (.308 Cal) “5R” polygonal right handed 1x10 twist button rifled barrels.
Hogan X-Brake 5 prong muzzle brake and collar nut, which is remarkably effective in recoil reduction but it does not suppress the flash. Made by Hogan Guns.

LOWER RECEIVER:
Billet machined from 7075-T6 aircraft aluminum alloy with integral oversized trigger guard for use with heavy gloves.
Wire E.D.M.’d flared Magwell, ambidextrous bolt release lever machined into the lower receiver. Finished in black, O.D. Green, Tan or Clear anodize, NP3™ or Cerakote™ Dark Earth or O.D. Green colors.

PISTOL GRIP and STOCKS:
ERGO™ pistol grip, VLTOR™ 6-position retractable buttstock with Mil-Spec tube.
Non slip special compound rubber butt pad. Reversible for right or left handed shooters.
Finished in black, O.D. Green, Tan or Clear anodize, NP3™ or Cerakote™ Dark Earth or O.D. Green colors.

TRIGGER:
HOGAN “Gold Standard”™ trigger system, 4.5 lb. non-adjustable pull, (for zero failure) single stage competition trigger.
Trigger, hammer & disconnector E.D.M.’d from A2 tool steel. Melonite heat treated for long life.
Pin tubes are black oxide coated 8620 steel. Housing precision machined from 6061 billet aluminum. Deep gold anodize finish. High temp silicone cord base cushions.
Complete with KNS™ precision non-rotating pins.

MAGAZINES:
Although we utilize P-MAG LR-308™ magazines, HOGAN firearms will fit Bushmaster, DPMS, Fulton, JP Rifles, Knights, Remington R-25, Magpul™, original AR-10 waffle magazines and any Mil-Spec .308 magazine.
Optional: (Norgon™ “Ambi catch”™ mag release).

SIGHTS: (optional)
HOGAN front sight
HOGAN flip-up rear sight
HOGAN front and rear sight kit made by TROY™ Industries.

WEIGHT:
9 lbs. 2 oz (Tactical X-Rail)
9 lbs. 1 oz. (Hunter X-Rail)
9 lbs. 15 oz (Tactical X-Rail with PRS)
9 lbs. 14 oz. (Hunter X-Rail with PRS)

LENGTH:
  35 3/4 inches (collapsed)
  39 3/4 inches (extended)

NP3™ Plating:
NP3™ plating: combination of a nickel alloy plating combined with Polytetrafluoethylene (Teflon). NP3™ metal finish offers many benefits.
NP3 permits firing for longer periods of time between cleaning, dirt and powder residue have no wet or oily surface to cling to.
When cleaning is required, the effort needed is minimal - usually requiring only a soft cloth.

CERAKOTE™:
With a unique ceramic backbone, Cerakote™ firearm coatings improve performance and reliability over conventional finishes.
This state-of-the-art coating technology out-performs any competitive coating in both laboratory settings and real world applications.

A New Era of Perfection "The beginning of a new era of perfection", is how Blaser CEO Bernhard Knoebel has named the launch of the new Blaser bolt action rifle R8 in his preface of the brand-new catalog. For the past five years, there has been one lingering question for the hunters and engineers at Blaser, regarding the Blaser bolt action rifle R93: How can this technically superior concept be taken to the next level? In order to answer this question the Blaser engineers, most of them passionate hunters themselves, kept a close connection to hunters around the world in order to respond to their requests. Detachable Magazine When the development of the R8 actually started the detachable magazine was right at the top of the optimization list. Blaser found an ergonomically superior solution that essentially supports fast and intuitive handling. Magazine and trigger unit merged into one compact module. The magazine buttons are positioned right above the trigger guard. Thus, the magazine can be released blindly and within a split second. When removing the magazine, the R8 automatically de-cocks and once the magazine is removed, the cocking slide cannot engage anymore. Today, this is a very important safety feature securing the rifle against misuse by unauthorized persons. Blaser Precision Trigger The detachable magazine is just one of a multitude of innovations that turn the R8 into the new worldwide benchmark when it comes to bolt action rifles. Enhancing the reliable and precise performance of the trigger posed a very special engineering challenge that has been brilliantly mastered. The new Blaser Precision Trigger breaks crisp as glass at a trigger pull of 750 gram / 1 5/8 lbs. Thanks to its extremely short release time it turns the shooter’s thought impulse immediately into an accurate shot. The innovative design does not rely on a spring to reset the trigger after firing, which marks the next leap in rifle technology. The desmodromic trigger mechanism offers unsurpassed reliability in extreme conditions such as freezing rain and blowing dust. Perfect Stock In order to make shooting with the R8 as comfortable and safe as possible, Blaser attached immense importance to optimizing the stock, reaching a new level of perfection here, too. Different from traditional stock shapes the straight comb of the R8 diverts recoil forces horizontally on the shoulder. This results in increased muzzle stability and a substantial reduction of felt recoil. Thanks to a steeper angle, the palm support and a distinct cast, the R8 pistol grip provides a relaxed hand position allowing for controlled shooting and better shooting results. The Smith & Wesson Model 500 is a five-shot, single action/double-action large caliberrevolver produced by Smith & Wesson, firing the .500 S&W Magnum cartridge, a .50 caliber bullet.
It is built on S&W's largest frame, the X-Frame, which was developed because none of S&W's existing double-action frame designs could handle the muzzle energy and pressures generated by the .500 S&W cartridge.[2] It is the most powerful production revolver in the world today, and it is being marketed as being "the world's most powerful handgun" by the manufacturer.[3] There are a few other larger revolvers like for instance the Pfeifer Zeliska .600 Nitro Express revolver, however none of them are a "production" revolver. The Model 500 can fire a bullet weighing 350 gr ( 22.7 g; 0.8 oz) at 1975 feet per second (602 m/s) generating a muzzle energy of over 3,030 foot-pounds force (4.1 kJ).
Articles, statements, and opinions vary widely on this firearm. Any of the available bullet weights can be relied on to take game at a range in excess of 200 yards (183 m), a feat matched by only a handful of other handguns.[citation needed] The advanced design of the firearm helps in counteracting recoil felt by the shooter. This includes the sheer weight of the firearm, use of rubber grips, the forward balance, and the use of a compensator. On certain S&W Performance Center models the compensator is replaced with a full muzzle brake.
Like most big caliber handguns the Model 500 is suitable for sport and hunting applications. The high energy of these rounds make it possible to hunt extremely large African game successfully.[4
